NTRIBUTOR", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "<!--\r\nThank you for filing a bug report! \ud83d\udc1b Please provide a short summary of the bug,\r\nalong with any information you feel relevant to replicating the bug.\r\n-->\r\n\r\nI don't know if this should be filled on rust-analyzer or here. Feel free to move.\r\nI tried this code:\r\n\r\n```rust\r\n#[derive(Clone)] // <- Error here\r\nstruct S {\r\n\t#[cfg(feature = \"a_feature\")]\r\n\thi: String\r\n}\r\n\r\nfn main() {}\r\n```\r\n\r\nI expected to see this happen: *Nothing*\r\n\r\nInstead, this happened: Rust-analyzer triggers on `#[Derive(Clone)]` with the message `no such field`. This happens when any field of a struct is behind a `#[cfg]`. Note that using commands like `cargo check` or `cargo run` won't report this error. Only the LSP will report it.\r\n\r\nObviously, if `a_feature` is enabled by default, the error dissapears.\r\n\r\n### Meta\r\n\r\n`rustc --version --verbose`:\r\n```\r\nrustc 1.71.0-nightly (9ecda8de8 2023-04-30)\r\nbinary: rustc\r\ncommit-hash: 9ecda8de85ce893cc3fc748ab06be0b8250147a7\r\ncommit-date: 2023-04-30\r\nhost: x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu\r\nrelease: 1.71.0-nightly\r\nLLVM version: 16.0.2\r\n```\r\n\r\n<!--\r\nInclude a backtrace in the code block by setting `RUST_BACKTRACE=1` in your\r\nenvironment. E.g. `RUST_BACKTRACE=1 cargo build`.\r\n-->\r\n<details><summary>Backtrace</summary>\r\n<p>\r\n\r\n**N/A**\r\n\r\n</p>\r\n</details>\r\n", "closed_by": null, "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/111281/reactions", "total_count": 0, "+1": 0, "-1": 0, "laugh": 0, "hooray": 0, "confused": 0, "heart": 0, "rocket": 0, "eyes": 0}, "timeline_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/111281/timeline", "performed_via_github_app": null, "state_reason": null}